# After Effects → CapCut AI Converter

## Environment Variables

Erstelle eine `.env` Datei im Root-Verzeichnis:

```bash
# Database
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=yourpassword
DB_NAME=ae_to_capcut

# CapCut API
CAPCUT_API_URL=https://api.capcut.com
CAPCUT_API_KEY=your_api_key

# Model Config
AI_DEVICE=cuda  # oder cpu
```

## Setup

```bash
# Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/SymCheck/ae-to-capcut-ai.git
cd ae-to-capcut-ai

# Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Copy .env example
cp .env.example .env
```

## Usage

### Single Project Conversion

```bash
python main.py --mode convert \
  --input data/raw_ae_projects/project.json \
  --output data/capcut_projects/project_capcut.json
```

### Batch Conversion

```bash
python main.py --mode convert-batch \
  --input data/raw_ae_projects/ \
  --output data/capcut_projects/
```

### With Style Transfer

```bash
python main.py --mode convert \
  --input data/raw_ae_projects/project.json \
  --output data/capcut_projects/project_capcut.json \
  --style-transfer
```

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── ai_model/          # Neural Networks & Training
├── video_processor/   # AE Parsing & CapCut Generation
├── utils/             # Config & Logger
└── api/               # FastAPI Routes (coming soon)
```

## Features Implemented

- ✅ After Effects JSON Parser
- ✅ Effects Mapper (AE → CapCut)
- ✅ Text Animation Support
- ✅ Keyframe Extraction
- ✅ Style Transfer Model (CNN + LSTM)
- ✅ Effect Classifier
- ✅ Keyframe Predictor
- ✅ Batch Processing
- ⏳ REST API (in progress)
- ⏳ GPU Optimization
- ⏳ Advanced Color Grading

## Next Steps

1. **Trainings-Daten sammeln**: AE + CapCut Projekte
2. **Modelle trainieren**: `python -m src.ai_model.train`
3. **API starten**: `python -m src.api.server`
4. **UI entwickeln**: Web-Interface für Conversions

